{"lemma": "سَبْتٌ", "slug": "سَبْتٌ", "root": "NTWS", "root_slug": "NTWS", "root_link": "/words/roots/NTWS", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun_prop", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "سَبْت", "root": "سبت", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 6}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n18645"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "Saturday", "fa": "شنبه", "ur": "ہفتہ", "tr": "Cumartesi", "id": "Sabtu", "bn": "শনিবার", "es": "sábado", "fr": "samedi", "de": "Samstag", "ru": "суббота", "zh": "星期六"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n18645", "headword_ar": "سَبْتٌ", "root": "sbt", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Rest:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quiet, stillness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "freedom from motion."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) [See 1, of which it is an inf. n.] See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subaAtN", "text_ar": "سُبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~abotu", "text_ar": "السَّبْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomu Als~aboti", "text_ar": "يَوْمُ السَّبْتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sabbath,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Saturday;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one of the days of the week;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the seventh of those days:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) so called because the creation commenced on the first day of the week and continued to [the end of] Friday, and on the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sbt", "text_ar": "سبت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "there was no creation, the work having ceased thereon: or, as some say, because the Jews ceased thereon from work, and the management of affairs: (M, TA:) or because the days [of the week] end thereon: (S, TA:) Az says that he errs who asserts it to have been so called because God commanded the Children of Israel to rest thereon, and that God created the heavens and the earth in six days, whereof the last was Friday, then rested, and the work ceased, and therefore He named the seventh day"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ywm", "text_ar": "يوم"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alsbt", "text_ar": "السبت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": this, he says, is an error, because [he affirms that]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabata", "text_ar": "سَبَتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning “ he rested ” is not known in the language of the Arabs, but signifies"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaEa", "text_ar": "قَطَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and rest cannot be attributed to God, because He knows not fatigue, and rest is only after fatigue and work: (TA:) the pl. [of pauc.] is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asobutN", "text_ar": "اَسْبُتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subuwtN", "text_ar": "سُبُوتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, M, Msb, K:)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1288}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it has no dim. (Sb, S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ams", "text_ar": "امس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabotN", "text_ar": "سَبْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A week; from the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabot", "text_ar": "سَبْت"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabot", "text_ar": "سَبْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the sabbath to the sabbath"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: so in the saying, in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famaA raA^ayonaA Al$~amosa sabotFA", "text_ar": "فَمَا رَاَيْنَا الشَّمْسَ سَبْتًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And we saw not the sun for a week"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: as when one says “ twenty autumns ” meaning “ twenty years: ” or it means in this instance"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a space of time, whether short or long."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "burohapN", "text_ar": "بُرْهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A space,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "period,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a long space"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "period,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (M, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mina Ald~ahori", "text_ar": "مِنَ الدَّهْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of time"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) so in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aqamotu sabotFA", "text_ar": "اَقَمْتُ سَبْتًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I remained, staid, dwelt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abode, a space,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a long space, of time"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabotapF", "text_ar": "سَبْتَةً", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanobatFA", "text_ar": "سَنْبَتًا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanobatatFA", "text_ar": "سَنْبَتَتًا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, K.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dahorN", "text_ar": "دَهْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Time;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a long time;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a space,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "period, of time, whether long or short;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subaAtN", "text_ar": "سُبَاتٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, M, K.) And [hence] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AibonaA subaAtK", "text_ar": "اِبْنَا سُبَاتٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The night and the day:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K:) Ibn Ahmar says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wakun~aA wahumo kaA@bonaYo subaAtK tafar~aqaA\n                      \n                     \n                        siwFY vum~a kaAnaA munojidFA watahaAmiyaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And we were, with them, like the night and the day that parted asunder alike, then became one going towards Nejd and one going towards Tihámeh"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, K:) such, they say, is the meaning: (S:) or, as IB says, on the authority of Aboo-Jaafar Mohammad Ibn-Habeeb,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AbnA sbAt", "text_ar": "ابنا سبات"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "were two men, one of whom saw the other in a dream, and then one of them awoke in Nejd, and the other in Tihámeh: or they were two brothers, one of whom went to the east to see where the sun rose, and the other to the west to see where it set. (L, TA.)       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain pace"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of camels:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a quick pace:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EanaqN", "text_ar": "عَنَقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]: (AA, S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a pace exceeding that termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEanaqu", "text_ar": "العَنَقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M.)       -A3-  A"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "swift,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or an"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "excellent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "horse; (K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that runs much."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-  A boy, or young man,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of bad disposition,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "illnatured, and bold,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "daring."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) ―         -b3-  A man"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cunning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "possessing intelligence,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sagacity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "intelligence mixed with craft and forecast; and excellent in judgment;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "very cunning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; (K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "silent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lowering his eyes, looking towards the ground;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subaAtN", "text_ar": "سُبَاتٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the same. (K, TA.) ―         -b4-  A man"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who sleeps much;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaviyru Als~ubaAti", "text_ar": "كَثِيرُ السُّبَاتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masobuwtN",